# CVE-2025-68121 - Go stdlib crypto/tls (incorrect certificate validation
# during TLS session resumption), found in the `gosu` binary bundled inside
# the official postgres:16-alpine image (used internally by Postgres's
# docker-entrypoint.sh to drop from root to the postgres user at container
# startup). gosu never initiates or accepts a TLS connection - it has no
# reachable attack surface for this CVE in our usage. Waiting on the
# upstream postgres image to rebuild with a newer gosu (Go 1.24.13+/1.25.7+).
CVE-2025-68121
